Check out the Iris Dataset

WHAT TYPES OF PREDICTION ERROR
- Training Set Error = Training Error (running the model on the training data)
- Test Set Error = Generalization Error
- Out of Sample Data Error (error in real life) 

Overfitting: Traning Error goes down while generalization (test) error goes up

How well does generalization error predict oos accuracy?
	-- > not well because generalization gives a high variance estimate of oos accuracy
	-- > cross validation... fitting your model a number of times
			- get a more robust estimae of generalization error

Cross Validation
	- > can be done by shuffling feature space, or by shuffling records
	- > Nested Cross Validation -- Outer loop is the feature space - inner is the sample data


two ways of training LRession model
	- > maximum likleyhood
	- > sgd (better for bigger data set)

CONFUSION MATRIX

						ACTUAL 
					|--------------
Predicted	|TP  		|  FP |
					|FN  		|	 TN |

True Positinve Rate  :  TP / TP+FN (good stuff)
False Positive Rate  :  FP / FP+TN (bad stuff)


ROC Curve - Classification Model Performance
	- Area Under the Curve.. Summary statistic for Model Performance


